13 October 2015Deputy Minister of Communications, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams will address the Gala dinner at the Film and Publication Conference (FPB), on Tuesday, 13th October 2015.The FPB, in collaboration with International Association of Internet Hotlines (INHOPE), is currently hosting the first African Media Content Classification and Online Child Protection Conference from 11 to 14 October 2015 at the Misty Hills Country Hotel and Conference Centre.The conference attended by delegates from South Africa and other countries in the SADC region and Sub-Saharan Africa intends to examine issues surrounding cyber safety, child protection and content classification from an African perspective.The details of the event are as follows:Date: 13 October 2015 Time: 18h00 22h00 Venue: Casalinga Ristorane Italiano Muldersdrift, Johannesburg, GautengEnquiries: Mzimasi Ngqelu Cell: 076 904 3557Email: mzi@doc.gov.zaIssued by Ministry of Communications